This is not a good app. You enter a depth you want your plug (rapala, bandit, ect.) to run. Then you enter a couple of variables, and then it tells you how much line to put out. Except it doesn't change with speed! At all! And the calculations are of from my experience! Telling me to put out 14' of line to pull a shallow flicker shad 6' deep at any speed!
replyContent: It is accepted that the depth of such a rig doesn't vary with speed if you are running at normal trolling speeds with mono or braid. This is because all of the forces on such a rig are all proportional to speed. You can verify this by observing that the angle between your line and the water will not vary as you change speed. Email for more info.

content: I recently got into leadcore fishing and had gone out 3 times with no luck. I was just counting colors to estimate depth.
